deck_excerpt: A Homebrew Decklist i made for fun and my list for coming back to my favourite archtype invoked and tons of tech cards that i played for fun.
deck_description:
This Deck is pretty basic for those with common knowledge about doing combos so the main combo revolves around Aleister the Invoker + Two Light Extenders So for this case the two light extenders are Photon Thrasher and Mekk-Knight Purple NightFall
  1. Special Summon Photon Thrasher and then Normal Summon Aleister and search Invocation.
  2. This is optional but u can turn Aleister to Almiraj depending on your hand.
  3. Using Aleister and Photon Thrasher make Aleister Invoker of Madness
  4. Set Invocation in the same column as Madness and special Summon Nightfall (using its effect is recommend)
  5. Use your Invocation and summon Mechaba using Aleister and Photon Thrasher in Grave
  6. Use Madness effect to discard and add Invocation to your hand.
  7. Use Invocation Grave effect to add Aleister the Invoker back to your hand (You will need it)
  8. Then Using Invoked Mechaba and Nightfall since both our light summon Union Carrier to the left zone madness is pointing(optional)
  9. Now activate Invocation in your hand fusing Aleister in hand and Nightfall in Grave the make Mechaba.
  10. Activate Madness to discard adding Invocation to hand.
  11. Than for the final time activate Invocation to summon your last Mechaba using Aleister in Grave + Mechaba to make your final Mechaba.
  12. Xyz Summon Calamitas using both of the Invoked Mechaba and use Union Carrier effect to Equip that Buster Dragon to lock Extra deck
  13. Bonus Tips: If you somehow get a extra extender to utilize than you can also end with Elysium.
Meaning Your Board is usually a Skill Drain + Extra Deck Lock and a Board wipe occasionally. Weakness is a freaking Kaiju like legit if you get rid of calamitas your extra deck lock is gone. Also Nibiru hurts the deck i wouldnt say this deck is meta relevant it is weak to handtraps. Also Dark Ruler No More is GG vs This Deck.

deck_excerpt: A fun, fish-themed deck, that relies on building up your aquatic forces behind cover and swamping your enemies when they least expect it.
deck_description: A fun, fish-themed deck, that relies on building up your aquatic forces behind cover and swamping your enemies when they least expect it.     Notable Cards: Hyper-Ancient Shark Megalodon, Shark Drake, Poseidra The Atlantean Dragon, A Legendary Ocean, Tornado Wall, Atlantean Attack Squad.  Although the deck doesn't consist of incredibly powerful cards that can win the game in a single attack, it requires careful placement and an effective plan of attack to use effectively.  Atlantean Attack Squad and Mystical Space Typhoon are effective at keeping the board clean while you attempt to build your forces. In the event where Atlantean Attack Squad is destroyed, it can be recovered by using salvage.  A Legendary Ocean and Tornado wall are the driving point of this deck, protecting your weaker monsters such as Starfish and Jellyfish while you prepare to Xyz or tribute summon for Shark Drake or Hyper-Ancient Shark Megalodon.  Before battling take note that Hyper-Ancient Shark is a CRUCIAL unit as its ability to destroy a monster you opponent controls after dealing damage can deal with monsters that are a great deal stronger then it. if it can attack any monster on the field, fish depth charge can deal with them for you or you can power up Megalodon with aqua-jet

The reason why you'd play this over the Eldlich is because of VFD (what does the actual acronym stand for?), Naturia Beast, and for the level 2 Karakuri negate searches (how awesome is it that it can search for a Karakuri Infinite Impermanence or a Negate S/T at SS 3?!).     I don't think it needs to Lvl 9 Gizmek Kaku, but I don't think it's bad, either.
this is a go second deck if you do need to go first it will still do well

This Trickstar deck uses the OCG only card Trickstar Fez. It is a really good card that literally is an instant Holly angel because it provides 2 tokens. Otherwise it can be used for  more burning if you already have an angel on the field. You can use Set Rotation or Terraforming to get a mystic mine or Trickstar Light Stage to the field, whichever one you need. A play I like to make is using Set Rotation to set Light Stage to my field and Mine to the other when my opponent has more monsters. This way They will either have to activate Mine to get rid of Light Stage, blocking all attacks and monster effects from him, or leave the Mine set, not allowing him to destroy Light Stage.  My Rating:  Attack: 3/5  Defense: 4/5  Consistency: 4/5  Strong Against: Adamancipator, Exodia  Weak against: True Draco, Vanity  Combos:  Cards in hand: Trickstar Fez, Trickstar Candina  Activate Fez, summoning 2 tokens  Link summon Holly Angel with the tokens  Normal summon Candina into a zone Holly angel points to, allowing the 200 damage  Activate Candina's effect, add Light Stage to the hand  Activate Light Stage and add Lilybell to the hand  Chain Lilybell's effect to Special summon herself to a zone Holly angel points to, dealing 200 damage + another 200 Lightstage damage  Link Lilybell into Bloom, doing 400 damage  Link Candina and Bloom into Crimson Heart, dealing 400 damage  Activate Crimson Heart if you want to, but it won't yield 2 cards  Link them all into a Bella Madonna, then activate her effect to do 1000 damage + another 200 damage from Light Stage  Total damage: 200 + 400 + 400 + 400 + 1000 + 200 =2600 damage     This deck is a very fun deck to play. It can be hard to make some combos at first but you'll get used to it. Have fun!

deck_excerpt: Just a basic Crusadia Kaiju OTK-based deck
deck_description: Crusadia Kaiju Deck 2020 Basic Crusadia Kaiju deck, if you're wondering why I used the Sky Striker cards it's because in this OTK based deck you can't afford to experience interruptions. You can change out the Sky Striker cards, I just used them and they seemed like an extra utility just in case your opponent tried to stop your play. You can also change out Monster Reborn for World Legacy Succession because you can search for it with Worl Legacy - World Crown, but even though that's there, Monster Reborn seemed more versatile than Succession because it doesn't limit you to special summoning to a zone a link monster points to. Back to the Sky Striker cards, the links can be replaced with other cards like Borrelsword Dragon or another boss monster. But normally with this deck, you won't have a turn 3 because you will most likely OTK your opponent.

deck_excerpt: Ever wanted to play Adamancipator in trinity format? This is the deck for you.
deck_description:
Strengths: 

Union Carrier lets you play the grind game with many other explosive decks Block Dragon is a great advantage maker that lets you tool box your entire deck and its protection helps push through boards. Has a very high ceiling when you open power cards such as Brilliant Fusion, Last Will, and Adamancipator excavations Can stun very well with Ties of the Brethren and Koa'ki Meiru

Weaknesses:

Can open very bricky hands (Solid Bricks) Very GY depended deck; Called by and Cosmic Cyclone hurt the deck a lot

Trinities:

2x Last Will (Extra Unlimited Card) 2x Brilliant Fusion (Extra Unlimited Card) 2x Adamancipator Researcher (Extra Unlimited Card)

Comments:

Union combo is summoning Union Carrier while you still control a Rock-type Monster and equipping Block Dragon from the deck The deck can do unfair plays such as ending on multiple Xyzs/Synchros if you get luckly with the Adamancipator Beta The Electromagnet Warrior is a 1 card Berserkion the Electromagna Warrior with 1 pop on summon (takes 2 turn)
  1. Normal Beta, Search Alpha The Electromagnet Warrior
  2. On the opponent's turn use Beta to tag out into Delta The Magnet Warrior, use its effect to foolish Gamma The Electromagnet Warrior
  3. On your turn summon Alpha search Berserkion, banish Gamma, Beta, Alpha from the field/gy to summon him from hand and banish Delta to pop a card (not once per turn)
The Side decked rocks are all searchable with Gallant Granite and can be summoned with Super Team Buddy Force Unite! Doki Doki is also a recruiter that summons from deck, with a low cost and can be used as an extender Brilliant Fusion doubles as a free body as well as a foolish for all rocks/Painful Decision Ties of the Brethren works as a combo finisher (at the end of Union Combo) or as a stun option (worth spending Trinitys on if you want to toolbox) Last Will helps with Union Combo and toolboxing from deck Adamancipator Risen - Dragite is a blowout card that can break boards (and gains protection form Block Dragon) Barrier Statue of the Drought + Koa'ki Meiru Overload is to much for most non Earth decks to handle, and you can turn off your own Barrier by turning it into Gallant

deck_excerpt: A variation of my last Dragma Cyber Angel deck
deck_description: After playing my last deck i decided to make a variation of it that uses the all new card - Diviner of Heralds. That card is really OP in this deck because if you can't send Herald of the Arc Light to the GY, you can use your Cyber Angels instead. it will also benefit Cyber Angel Vrash, giving it a guaranteed negate. To see my last decklist (which is the original deck i modified from) look here. My rating: Attack: 4/5 Defense: 5/5 Consistency: 4/5 Strong Against: General decks that love the extra deck, e.g. Salamangreat, Invoked Weak Against: Altergeist, Mystic Mine Burn/Exodia Combos: (In hand: Diviner of Heralds, Machine Angel Ritual) Normal summon Diviner of Heralds Activate its effect, sending Herald of the Arc Light from the Extra deck to the GY Activate Arc light, add Cyber Angel Idaten to the hand. Activate your Ritual, summon Idaten using Diviner as a tribute. Diviner's effect activates as it was tributed; summon Cyber Petit Angel from the deck. Chain Idaten's effect and add Machine Angel Absolute Ritual to the hand. Activate Petit angel's effect, add Vrash to the hand. Ritual summon Vrash with Cyber Petit Angel, Idaten and Diviner in the GY. Idaten's effect activates, turning your Vrash into a 4k beatstick permanently. Note that adding 1000 atk to Vrash isn't Vrash's effect, so using impermanence or veiler won't remove it. one of the ways to stop this is by activating Called by the Grave to banish Idaten after the Ritual summon.   Dragma combo: Activate Disciples of the Nadir, search for Ecclesia, sending Bastard to the GY Normal summon Ecclesia, add Dogmatic Nation to the hand Activate Dogmatic Nation so your opponent will risk losing a monster if they attack Ecclesia End your turn. At the End Phase Bastard in the GY will activate, allowing you to SS Maximus Dragma from the deck. Have fun!

deck_excerpt: An MBT inspired deck, a super reliable deck thanks to Crystron Halqifibrax, Deskbot 001 & 003, MPB Auroradon as supports to call strong Synchro and Xy
deck_description: Make sure to review of the cards individually to apply this steps, to, 'cuz it hards on explain through text y'know. Example, if you have of this card/2cards in your first draw: summons Deskbot 003, > 001 > Halqifibrax > 001> Auroradon >(3)token > (2)001> Coltwing >(2)token > 001 > Herald > Quandax > F.A > Borrel > Nekroz. (This combo can do negates a lot, it is recommendable if your turn is first) note: Herald is used to add Nekroz to your hand by tributing to the GY using the second effect of Auroradon to call Coltwing to the field. note: 001 is summoned from the GY if two machine type tokens is summoned at the sametime.   2nd combo: it's the same combo as the first one but a little different. You can only call Superdreadnought xyz monster in the end if you have atleast 1 lvl 4 Mecha Phantom Beast in your hand. (Best to use this combo if your turn is second and if your opponent haven't done right in his first turn because of your negates using of your handtrap) Halqifibrax's effect is use to special summon O-Lion instead, then:  special summon Auroradon > (1)token > (3)token > 001 > lvl7 synchro monster > Coltwing > (2)token > 001 > Borrel > lvl4 any MPB monster > Superdreadnought Rail > Superdreadnought Jugger. note: MPB O-Lion's effect can special summon 1 token when it sent to the graveyard. Also you can use the effect to normal summon 1 MPB monster from you hand by banishing O-lion to the GY. note: lvl4 MPB monster's level adjust depends to the counts of lvl3 token on the field. Two tokens on the field can make MPB monsters lvl10 to xyz summon rank10 monster. Other cards to access the combo: (note: once you have 1tuner and 1tuner or 1monster to special summon Halqifibax and having 001 or more to the GY, you can full access the combo. Scrap Recycler: use the effect to send Jet Synchron to the GY Jet Synchron: you can use this to link summon Linkuriboh. You can activate this card's effect in the GY and special summon to the field by sending 1 card from your hand to the GY(send 001 if you do have). Instant Fusion: to summon 1 tuner or 1 effect Fusion monster for summoning Halqifibrax purposes. World Legacy Inheritor: useful when you special summon Linkuriboh on the field and use this Spell card to special summon that link material to the field. Foolish Burial: you can send 1 Jet Synchron or 1 Deskbot 001 from your deck to the GY. One for One: use to discard 1 card to the GY then special summon 1lvl1 (001 or Jet Synchron) monster to the field. Ash blossom and Ghost Ogre: use this much cards to negate, and you can also use this for material in link summoning if there's no choice. Emergency Teleport: to call Ghost Ogre from Hand or Deck to the field for emergency only! O-Lion: is also useful in some situations. Once this card is sent to the GY, you can special summon 1token. And also can banish O-Lion to free normal summon 1MPB monster from your hand. Nibiru: not much use at all. If you have this on your hand and your opponent doing combos....BOOM Conclusion: In the mid game if your opponent manages to destroy your succeed summoning combo. 70% chance to summon Auroradon (also thanks to the 001's and O-Lion) that can make easy way to fill your monster zone and make a comeback. Many ways to be creative, 90%  ways to access the combo in your first turn that is why it is the best. Can also beat the current Meta...nowadays mr5 that's all thanks for reading.

deck_description: When you play this deck, all you need is start first than your opponent, and have in your hand only 2 cards to set-up the lockdown, but be aware that this play is easily counterable; cards like Infinite Impermanence, Nibiru the primal being, etc. Combos: Your first combo is: use Numeron Network to bring the Numbers 1,2,3 and 4, (if you had in your hand Memories of Hope, you are allowed to use and draw 4 cards, that is absolutely insane!) if you can battle, do it, because of their effect that allows you to probably OTK your opponent. If you don't, just use them to summon our deck boss Number S0: Utopic ZEXAL, and force your opponent to quarantine. And if you had the Generaider Boss Stage, don't worry and use it, so in the opponent turn you can summon a Generaider Boss of your choice and up to 4 Generaider Tokens; you can use the tokens either to use the effects of the Generaider Bosses or to Summon the Trias Hierarchia, Tributing 3 of those tokens you are able to destroy 1 enemy card and also draw 2 Cards. Another useful combo is summoning Accesscode Talker, if you had in your hand the Effect Veiler, you can normal summon him, and if you already had a monster on the field you can Link Summon the Crystron Halqifibrax, and due to their effect you can bring another Effect Veiler, from you, deck or graveyard, and if you do, use them to special summon Selene, Queen of the Master Magicians, but be aware that you need at least 3 spell cards in the field or both players graveyard, so, you can bring back the Effect Veiler and use them to Link Summon the Accesscode Talker, active their effect in Selene' in order to gain 3000 atk points, and he is also able to destroy up to  2 cards on the field by banishing the 2 link monsters used in this combo. this is a generic combo, but very effective though. Deck: Numeron Generaider Boss. Type: Lockdown, OTK. Difficulty: 5/10. Handiness/Consistency: 6/10 (the first turn matter? yes. How many cards do you need to extract 100% of this deck? 2 initial cards. It is easily counterable? yes). Draw power: 4/10, Conditional (can I use pot of desires? no). Recovery: 2/10. Comeback: 4/10. "This deck is recommended for Medium duelists, Average final turn: 5". The perfect initial hand at the first turn: Numeron Network, Generaider Boss stage, Trias Hierarchia, Memories of Hope, and 1 bait card -like terraforming or planet pathfinder. The perfect initial hand at Second turn: Numeron Network, Generaider Boss stage, Dark Ruler no More, Nibiru the primal being, Lightning Storm, and Memories of hope. so, as you can see, all we need is Numeron Network and Generaider Boss stage, and both are field spells that can be easily searched, by cards like terraforming, planet pathfinder, numeron wall, generaider boss fight, etc. I hope everyone could enjoy this guide, I pretend to make more guides in the future, If you want to make constructive criticism or add more information, feel free to comment below! That is it, folks! my name is Randall and I see y'all on the battlefields!

deck_name: TIME MACHINE (not the Time Machine trap card)
deck_excerpt: Consistent access to Time Wizard and Time Magus or Auroradon/Accesscode to break board while using tuner combo for Borreload Savage + Herald Arc Light
deck_description: The slightly better than Time Wizard card, Time Magus, finally has been revealed. Both of those cards are super easy to fetch, Time Wizard by using Fusion Deployment and Time Magus by Instant Fusion (can be via Verte too, means you can wipe the board anytime with 2 monsters). Going first, we use regular Halqifibrax/Auroradon combo for Borreload Savage and Herald of the Arc Light, while the going second strat has many ways to break the board. The Scrap lineup is very versatile, not only it can go to Halqifibrax, it also provides backup combo while can fetch Time Wizard via Desperado Barrel Dragon for further grindy game. Mathematician, Scrap Recycler (free link 4 or Verte while searching Time Wizard), Jet Synchron, and Tuning are our starter, making us playing 11 starters. Ghost Ogre (Crossout target, can replace it depends on popularity), 2 )-Lion (ensures Auroradon effect), 2 Time Wizard (easily searchable, its effect aint that good too), Magicalized Fusion (free Time Magus for late game), One Day of Peace (prevents damage from both Time Magus and Wizard), 3 Second Coin Toss (for big brain gamble), Millenium Eyes Restrict (negate discarded monster handtrap), Borreload Dragon (non-targeting non-destruction monster removal), Auroradon (combo piece, non-targeting destruction), Scrap Wyvern (backup combo, non-targeting destruction), Secure Gardna (prevents taking damage, summoned via Linkuriboh), Linkuriboh (enables Jet Synchron to Halqifibrax). Pros: Super consistent, great going first or second while still have follow up play, have big slot for staples. Cons: Both Time Magus and Wizard are gamble.

deck_excerpt: A Consistent Dragon Link deck with a Red-Eyes twist which enables stronger boards. Combo videos, explanation of Red-Eyes engine, and budget options in
deck_description: Index: 1 Intro 2 Red-Eyes Engine/cards 3 Combos 4 Budget options 5 Side Deck   1 Intro This is a Dragon Link deck that does Dragon Link deck things but with a Red-Eyes twist added in. Namely, I’ve expanded the Red-Eyes engine in the deck to exploit Black Metal Dragon’s effect not being a hard once per turn. I’ve also updated the deck with Eternity Code’s Noctovision Dragon and found Room to add a couple Pot of Avarices. Pot of Avarice gives the deck a lot more recycling of resources to play longer games than a normal Dragon Link deck would be able to. I have also done an extensive number of test hands to determine that this deck is just as consistent as a conventional competitive Dragon Link deck while making stronger boards.   2 Red Eyes Engine/cards The Red-Eyes cards are present for the most part not to make a Red-Eyes board but to smooth out or slightly beef up conventional Dragon Link combos. The primary way the deck expects to acquire these cards is by sending Black Metal Dragon to the GY. Red-Eyes Malefic can be used to turn a Romulus into a Hieratic before the deck Dark locks itself. Red-Eyes Alternative exists if you draw the normal Red-Eyes or don’t have a field spell to play Malefic. Red-Eyes Fang with Chain can target Red-Eyes Darkness Metal Dragon and add another disruption onto your board.   I took out Borreload Dragon for a Red-Eyes Flare Metal Dragon because it fit thematically and there are enough lvl7 monsters to summon him somewhat reliably. That said I’m not sold that this card is actually a good pick and can be replaced with another extra deck monster or the original Borreload Dragon if you aren’t sold on him either.   3 Combos Here are some Youtube videos of different combos you’ll be looking for in this deck and how to perform them (Each video is about a minute long). Notably these combos are all done with minimum resources and can end on stronger boards with more resources invested. 1 card combo with Black Metal Dragon https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3TDyHNmjLwA 2 card combo with Rokket and Noctovision Dragon https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tSwGUosIoAo 2 card combo with Rokket and Quick Launch https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-BUC_x_3lBU 2 card combo with Rokket and Absorouter Dragon https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ny6Rl6a24V4 Playlist with all Combos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL4wvY6W8_pobhm2edgCy0rZypqEcJbtdX 4 Budget Options 3x Dark Ruler No more -> Effect Veiler is a good budget handtrap 3x Called by the Grave -> D.D. Crow. Doesn’t protect your combos but is a really strong affordable hand trap right now. 1x Borreload Savage Dragon -> Draco Berserker of the Tenyi is much weaker but still provides a strong level 8 synchro disruption to end on. 1x Borrelsword Dragon -> Borreload Dragon 1x Red-Eyes Fang with Chain -> another Red-Eyes B. Dragon or else any other card you so choose. This card should be reprinted in Legendary Duelists: Season 1 so it should come down in price (hopefully).   Other budget options: Borreload Excharge Dragon, and Borrelguard Dragon, the Topologic Monsters, Galaxy Satellite Dragon, Barricadeborg Blocker, Saryuja, Wee Witch’s Apprentice, and Booster Dragon.   5 Side Deck There are so many options for the side deck at the moment at so many different price points I felt that I didn’t want to hold the deck back or make it really expensive by trying to recommend a specific side deck. Feel free to use whatever tech cards you think are best for current meta.

deck_name: Vanity Dragma Cyber Angel Lock May 2020
deck_excerpt: Lock your opponent out of special summoning with Vanity's ruler. I also put a dragma engine in to deal with threats from the extra deck.
deck_description: Using the new Dragma cards as a toolbox, this deck can lock your opponent out of special summoning pretty easily and swarm the field with cyber angels. The Herald of Perfection is used as an omni-negate. what's good about it though is that is isn't once per turn, as long as you have a fairy in your hand. I dislike running too many impcantations as they brick if you don't have a ritual card in your hand. The extra deck is purely used for the Dragmas to destroy (except Herald of Mirage Lights) so don't try to get them on the board!  My rating:  Attack: 5/5  Defense: 4/5  Consistency: 3/5  Strong Against: General decks that love the extra deck, e.g. Salamangreat, Invoked  Weak Against: Altergeist, Mystic Mine Burn/Exodia  Dragma combo:  Activate Disciples of the Nadir, search for Ecclesia, sending Bastard to the GY  Normal summon Ecclesia, add Dogmatic Nation to the hand  Activate Dogmatic Nation so your opponent will risk losing a monster if they attack Ecclesia  End your turn. At the End Phase Bastard in the GY will activate, allowing you to SS Maximus Dragma from the deck.     Vanity Lock combo:  Get any 2 impcantations onto the field, searching for Benten and/or Machine Angel Ritual if you don't have them  Ritual any monster using Benten as a tribute  Benten's effect now activates, adding a Vanity's Ruler to the hand  Normal summon Vanity's ruler, using the Impcantations as tributes.  Vanity's Ruler stops your opponent from Special Summoning completely, meaning he can't even use Kaijus to get rid of your monsters.     Also, if you want to add in a Dragma engine into your deck, here it is :  1 Maximus Dragma  2-3 Ecclesia  3 Disciple of the Nadir  1 Dogmatic Nation  1-3 Bastard the Ashen Dragon  1 Psy-framelord Omega (for recycling your cards)  Any removal/versatility that your deck lacks, like N'tss for targeted destruction or Wind Pegasus for a Knightmare Unicorn-like effect.  Hope you like this deck and the Dragma engine! Have fun!

deck_excerpt: And before you ask...Yes, this IS a JoJo reference!   (And also a meta deck)
deck_description: I never expected a Trap Monster deck like Eldlich to become meta. I ALSO didn't expect it to work well with Invoked.  I've been using my time in the coronavirus outbreak to 1: Wrap my head around this, and 2: Binge watch JoJo's Bizarre Adventure. I just finished Part 5 of JoJo, and given the concept of Stands and the gold theme, I decided that "Golden Wind" was the perfect name for my Eldlich Invoked deck.     It functions just as you would expect Eldlich Invoked would: As a control deck that can occasionally do good going second. If going first, your goal is to set up a board of as many disruptions as you can and MUDA MUDA your opponent's plays. If going second, your goal is to break apart your opponent's field so they can say ARRIVEDERCI to their Life Points.

deck_description: a dragunity deck with the support of tempes dragon ruler of storms, since it was limited to one copy i wanted to do something with it, so i built a dragunity deck including him and lightning for easy summoning, the main focus remains summoning synchro monsters like ascalon, that can banish enemy monsters as long as you have dragunity monsters in the graveyard, and with master rule 5 this is much easier, consistency is boosted by cards of consonance and trade-in, even if i'm gonna remove it alongside dragon shrine.  Now the main card in the deck, dragon ravine, is a dragunity search, a foolish burial for dragons and extends your plays by a lot, just keep sending your tuners to the graveyard and revive them for easy synchros, leyvaten plays a big role in the deck, he can revive himself if there's a equipped dragunity monster on the field, equip a tuner from the gy and go on a level 10 synchro.  Other plays involves dux or senatus and kuse, normal summoning one of the winged beasts guarantees a level 6 or 8 synchro like luin for further plays with kuse, gae bulg for dispaching problem monsters that you can't destroy via effects, gae dearg for adding a level 4 or lower winged beast or dragon at the cost of sending one to the graveyard, vajrayana for other level 8 synchros and crystal wing for negation.  Another layer to the strategy is the dragon ruler in this deck, even at one copy this bad boy can help you in so many ways, searching a wind attribute monster if banished, a dragon type monser if discarded alongside another wind monster and self reviving and returning to the hand, lightning the dragon ruler of draft is for easily bringing out the big guy.

deck_excerpt: One card makes True King OF All Calamities, Herald Of Protection with four negates, and Utopia Double for OTKing. With Generaider as a backup strat, a
deck_description: So, enough people have been asking for the decklist of the one-Halq four-negates-and-VFD-and-OTK combo I came up with that I decided to upload the more refined version. Long story short: It's a very consistent lockdown that, once put up, could only be brought down with a SuperPoly... but because it's so weak to disruption, about half the deck is dedicated to a Generaider backup strategy and generic disruption of my own.  This is a more refined version of a decklist I posted about a month ago, with some big improvements in the decklist and none in the actual combo.  (Quick breakdown: 20 one-card combo starters, 9 generaider field spells, 14 bricks, 17 disruptions)  ----------------------------  Basically, the whole deck exploits that Halqifibrax is a pseudo-FTK from only one card, and there's so very many cards that do that. So:  -60 cards instead of the usual 39 or 40. Normally, you want small decks so that you draw your best cards, but when you've got several dozen 'best cards', you want as large as you can to avoid drawing the combo bricks.  -Because you don't need to have more than one card for all this, you only need to use half your deck on this, which makes a whole bunch of room for disruptions and backup plays.  -Outside of generic disruption, there's basically only two options for non-normal-summoning, non-ED-using archetypes: Eldlich and Generaider. The advantage with Generaider is that it's *also* a one-card-starter archetype, so it leaves room for a heck-lot of disruption.  Hence, you have a deck that in a 5-card hand has an 88% chance of a pseudo-FTK, and a 57% chance of a Genraider Stage as backup, with an average of 1.4 disruption/going second cards.

deck_excerpt: The antimeta-ish version of the thunder family (or hunders).
deck_description: The antimeta-ish version of the thunder family (or hunders).

This deck makes use of the self destruction effects of the Machina monsters and the Meklords which take advantage of monsters being destroyed by card effects. Use the Machina monsters and their spell and traps to build field advantage set up bigger and bigger plays. Cards such as Machina overdrive and Machina Citadel to bring out the Meklord Emperors or set up the graveyard. You can also do the reverse and use the Meklords to bring out the Machinas in the graveyard, namely citadel by using the Meklords effects to destroy any earth machine to bring Citadel out of the graveyard or grabbing cards from the graveyard and putting them back into the hand with Machina defence perimeter which can also be used to make your Emperors untargetable by attacks and effects  The deck over all is very consistent and has tons of searching and recovery from all the search cards and recursion cards the two decks bring together.
